The paper may also belong to the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category as it deals with the generation of 3D shapes, which is a common topic in computer graphics. 

The paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a novel approach that utilizes a collection of parametric surface elements and a joint loss function to guide the distribution of points, which are common techniques used in machine learning. 

The paper may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category as it proposes a novel approach for completing a partial point cloud, which is a common task in artificial intelligence. 

Finally, the paper may also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category as it proposes a novel approach that utilizes a sampling algorithm to merge the coarse-grained prediction with the input point cloud, which is a common technique used in neural and evolutionary computing.
